text: Jelta Wong is a Papua New Guinean politician. He was first elected to the 10th National Parliament for the Gazelle Open seat in the 2017 General Elections as a United Resource Party candidate. He has been appointed as Minister for Health and HIV/AIDS in two separate terms both under Prime Minister James Marape, after being Minister for Police under Prime Minister Peter O'Neill. == References == Category:Living people Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Papua New Guinean politicians Category:National Parliament of Papua New Guinea
